'''Accessories''' are elements that can be placed on an avatar. They can be found in the '''Accessories''' section of the [[Avatar]] tab. Up to 5 accessories can be placed.

==Looks==
Accessed from the [[Avatar]] tab, the '''Looks''' section allow users to create and manage looks for the same, or different avatars. 

===Place accessories===
To place accessories on an avatar, start by creating a new look. Once created, select the look and click the "Modify" button. 

At this point, you will be thrown into a new window. From here, you can select accessories you own and place them on your avatar. Each accessory can be assigned a bone by clicking the "Attached to (x)" parameter in the Position tab. You may also rotate or scale them. 

The appearance of accessories, such as their color can be customized. Some accessories, such as the Google Eyes, have additional customizable elements, such as the Eye Spacing, the color of the Eyeball, Pupil, and Eyelash, or even the ability to toggle Eyelashes.

